| CeilingThreshold | num | Certain products are shipped in boxes (i.e. 24 chocolate bars in a box). If an order of 30 chocolate bars is given, it requires 1.25 boxes to be shipped. To decide whether to send 1 or 2 boxes for a product, fractional demand (i.e. 0.25) is compared to this threshold to decide if 1 or 2 box will be shipped. |

Step 1: Update the inventory levels at the beginning of the period:

This period's starting inventory is equal to the received quantity at this period plus the remaining inventory from previous period.

Step 2: Modify this period's starting inventory if manually provided inventory levels are present:

In some cases, starting inventory is required to be overwritten. ADDSTOCK field is given some positive number in those cases and if initial inventory is less than ADDSTOCK value, we modify it to be equal to ADDSTOCK. Moreover, if provided ADDSTOCK is negative, STARTSTOCK is reduced by ADDSTOCK level. If STARTSTOCK is negative, we equate it to zero.

Step 3: Update the inventory to be received (open order) levels:

Decrease the open order level by the received quantity

Step 4: Decide to order:

pen order) levels:

Decrease the open order level by the received quantity

Step 4: Decide to order:

Check if initial inventory plus the inventory to be received (on the way) is less than the minimum stock target. If yes, order up to maximum stock target

Step 5: Integrate case pack quantities:

Some products are shipped as a box containing certain number of items. In such cases, box capacities are important. Find the total number of boxes that will cover the order amount. If the last box has not been filled at least by CeilingThreshold and there is some inventory on the way, send the required number of boxes minus 1 box. Otherwise send the amount that will cover the order amount.

Step 6: Plan the upcoming inventory:

Ordered amount will be received after the specified lead time. Receive amount for the corresponding time period is updated.

Step 7: Update the inventory to be received (open order) levels:

responding time period is updated.

Step 7: Update the inventory to be received (open order) levels:

Open orders at the end of the day is equal to the order amount at this period plus the open orders from the previous period minus the received amount at this period.

Step 8: Perform the sales

If there is enough inventory to cover the demand, sales amount will be equal to the demand. Otherwise, the amount in STARTSTOCK at the beginning of this period will be sold.

Step 9: Update the inventory levels at the end of the period

The inventory level at the end of the period (ENDSTOCK) is equal to the initial inventory (STARTSTOCK) minus the amount sold.

Notes:

the period (ENDSTOCK) is equal to the initial inventory (STARTSTOCK) minus the amount sold.

Notes:

- If there is any receive quantity before simulation start date, input data should handle the start stock increase
- If simulation starts with openq input data should also handle the receive date. Simulation will receive those units in that day.
- Simdelayperiod>0 ken öncesindeki openq yürütmesi simulation delayperiod - 1 e kadar yapılmalı

SimData Input Control function ı yazılmalı

- stok targetmax >= stok target olmalı
- float  olmaması gereken yerler kontrolü
- negative stok sales kontrolleri
- data expanded olmalı (day orderların sıralı olması)
- sim ınputta olup rep infoda olmayan ikili olmamalı. bunu defaultlarla handle etmeliyiz
- Simdelay period=0 olunca 1.günden başlar
